<br>
<br>
When you PvP as a wizard, you nuke. You either kill everything, or you blow shit up pretty bad and get outta there. You don't stick around. If you have buddies with you, you either wait until the end (to insure you kill 'em before they gate or run away) and you cast shock of lightning on whoever you see casting spells.<br>
<br>
<br>
As far as nerfing *anything.* I odn't htink its right. A wizard can kill soemone in one blow. Whoopiee. But they're a sittign duck afterword and unless they're a plugger (people who don't get respect, just are considered weak fefs who would abuse their power regardless of MB or not), they know that MB is a last-ditch option for PvP. There are wiser things to do in PvP in its true form of fair engagement. <br>
<br>
<br>
Now granted. i don't htink you're goign to get to 60 with your wizard on Sullon, nor within the vicinity of worry anytime soon. You will still need to worry about HT. Yes, a wizard can be killed in one blow by an SK if he is low on health, or the SK is 8 levels above him or more. Big deal. once an SK usees his harm touch, he doesn't have it for another EQ day. That shouldn't really effect you very much. You're still gonna die some day. You're still gonna have to run once ina while, and a caster verse a melee always is a difficult fight unless you can start out with the upper hand. <br>
<br>
So, i'll say it again. I have about a 25% PvP success rate. That to me is pretty good, considering that includes times i'm ambushed, and times I have to gate and run away. I only die in pvP nowadays when I've just finished a brutal quad and am at 50% health or below, or I'm going into a fight I know I'm going to lose (Immortal healer/buffer, swarmmed by necros, etc).<br>
<br>
